# Testing Strategy

Per `docs/09-testing-strategy.md`:

## Layers

- **unit/** — domain rules, validation, policy, parsers, ranking (no I/O)
- **integration/** — PostgreSQL, pgvector, Neo4j, Redis/Celery, connectors (fixtures)
- **contract/** — OpenAPI, LLM schemas, repository interfaces, event schemas
- **e2e/** — register source → sync → approve → search → Q&A → graph browse

## Quality targets

- 100% schema-valid canonical writes
- 100% provenance on approved claims
- ≥95% source coverage for material answer claims (eval set)
- No unauthorized results in retrieval security tests
- Idempotent reprocessing of identical source versions
- Rebuildable Neo4j projection

## AI regression

Prompt/model/schema/ontology changes must run evaluation suite against baseline.

Do not weaken tests to pass. Add tests for new behavior.
